-- Red Bull’s Vettel Wins Pole Position for Malaysian Grand Prix
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-03-23T14:12:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-23/red-bull-s-vettel-wins-pole-position-for-malaysian-grand-prix.html
Red Bull’s Sebastian Vettel claimed
pole position for tomorrow’s Malaysian Grand Prix, beating out
Ferrari teammates Felipe Massa and Fernando Alonso.  Vettel, the defending world champion, posted a time of 1
minute, 49.674 seconds in his final run at the Sepang Circuit to
best Massa by 0.913 seconds. Alonso qualified third, more than a
second behind.  Lewis Hamilton of Mercedes, Red Bull’s Mark Webber and Nico Rosberg of Mercedes rounded out the top-six qualifiers. Lotus’s
Kimi Raikkonen, who won last week’s season-opening Australian
Grand Prix, was dropped to 10th in the starting grid after a
three-place penalty for impeding Rosberg.  The race, the second of 19 in the 2013 world championship,
is scheduled to start tomorrow at 4 p.m. local time.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  